---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import Avatar from '../components/Avatar.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
import PostCard from '../components/PostCard.astro';
import SocialLinks from '../components/SocialLinks.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
import { sortPostsByDate } from '../utils/blog';

const allPosts = await getCollection('blog', ({ data }) => !data.draft);
const latestPosts = sortPostsByDate(allPosts).slice(0, 5);
---

<BaseLayout narrow>
  <div class="page-cards">
    <Card class="intro">
      <div class="intro__header">
        <h1>About me</h1>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-6">
        My name is <strong>Benjamin Piouffle</strong>. I grew up believing that technology could be
        genuinely collaborative, that knowledge could be shared freely across borders by anyone who
        cared enough to contribute. That optimism hasn't fully survived contact with the modern
        internet which, somewhere along the way, became mostly a machine for selling things and harvesting
        attention.
      </p>
      <p>
        I care about the other side of that equation: open-source software, cooperative platforms,
        digital tools that actually empower the people who use them. If we're stuck with this timeline,
        we may as well find the cracks and see what else can be built with these tools.
      </p>
      <p>
        Day to day, I work as CTO of the Open Finance Consortium, a nonprofit behind{" "}
        <a href="https://opencollective.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >Open Collective</a
        > - an open-source platform built on a simple but underused idea: money flows should be
        transparent. Most large nonprofits and public institutions don't operate that way. We do.
        <br/>
        It's a small team with a wide scope and a lot of responsibility. My days span engineering,
        product, security, and the eternal challenge of getting humans to agree on how to build things.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm also the founder of{" "}
        <a href="https://captainfact.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CaptainFact</a
        >, a French nonprofit that came out of the rising tide of misinformation, and a conviction
        that the answer wasn't more top-down gatekeepers. I wanted something more horizontal: tools that let
        citizens verify claims together, in real time. The
        platform is still used, though it has more potential than it has had time to fulfill. What
        surprised me along the way is where the real impact seems to live: the association now runs
        critical thinking and media literacy workshops in schools, and I've come to believe that
        teaching young people how to evaluate sources might matter more than any tool I could ship.
      </p>
      <h2>About this site</h2>
      <p>
        This site exists for two things: presenting my work, and having a place to write. Not a
        newsletter, not a platform, just a personal corner of the internet to share ideas, things
        I've learned, and whatever I find worth putting into words.
      </p>
    </Card>

    <a class="cta" href="/about#about">
      More about my work
      <svg class="cta__icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <path
          d="M4 10h12M11 5l5 5-5 5"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="1.5"
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
      </svg>
    </a>

    <Card title="Latest posts">
      <ul class="post-list">
        {latestPosts.map((post) => <PostCard post={post} />)}
      </ul>
      {latestPosts.length > 0 && (
        <p class="mt-3">
          <a href="/blog/">View all posts</a>
        </p>
      )}
    </Card>

    <Card title="Connect">
      <SocialLinks />
    </Card>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
